 Ballet dancers wearing face masks perform onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines, Nov. 17, 2021. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali) MANILA, Nov. 18 (Xinhua) -- Ballet dancers wearing face masks perform onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines. The CCP is preparing to reopen their live theatre acts featuring dancers and choreographers who lost their jobs during the pandemic to support the country's dance industry.  The multiple exposure photo taken on Nov. 17, 2021 shows ballet dancers performing onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali)  Ballet dancers wearing face masks perform onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines, Nov. 17, 2021. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali)  Ballet dancers wearing face masks perform onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines, Nov. 17, 2021. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali)  Ballet dancers wearing face masks perform onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines, Nov. 17, 2021. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali)  The multiple exposure photo taken on Nov. 17, 2021 shows a ballet dancer performing onstage during a rehearsal for the resumption of theatre shows at the Cultural Center of the Philippines (CCP) in Pasay City, the Philippines. (Xinhua/Rouelle Umali) â– 